Tanzie was dropped off at a shelter when his previous owner passed away. He was clearly adored and itâ€™s easy to see why. Tanzie is a naturally happy, playful dog with humans and other dogs. He loves to chase and be chased. When he isnâ€™t playing he is a big snuggler. He loves to watch TV on the couch or sleep in the bed, if you let him. He is crate trained and walks well on a leash. Tanzie is about 3-4 years old, 7 pounds, and looks to be an Italian Greyhound/Miniature Pinscher Mix. He has been neutered and is fully vetted. He has been fostered since Hurricane Harvey in August 2017 and is good with other dogs and probably cats, and good with kids age 8 or older. To meet Tanzie contact Jamie's Animal Rescue at www.jamiesrescue.org

Do you believe everything happens for a reason? If you don't now, this story from @CARESClarksdale just might change your mind.
Sophie, pictured below, was brought to the CARES Clarksdale shelter after her owners moved and left her in the backyard. The shelter instantly fell in love with her and knew she was special. Sophie was unique to the CARES shelter, as they had never received a dog with a cleft lip.
The Humane Society of West Michigan soon visited the shelter and they were smitten by her gentle spirit. They opted to take Sophie with them for the chance of her finding her forever home.
In just a few weeks, Sophie found her perfect family... as a Cleft Lip Therapy Dog, nonetheless! Sophie now has a human brother with a cleft lip and she will soon become an office pup at the Cleft Lip Foundation in Michigan, where she will spread joy and encouragement to children and adults.
